{
  "texts": [
    "However, if the communication user is in the Mainlobe region, this strategy is not applicable.• IM.",
    "IM uses the indices of building blocks such as waveforms and subcarrier frequencies to represent communication symbols.",
    "It is a well-established idea that each communication symbol can be represented by a specific waveform [149,150].",
    "Moreover, Hassanien et al. [99] embedded the communication symbols into a transmitted signal via waveform permutation.",
    "For FH radar, Baxter et al. [97] proposed a signaling strategy based on FH code selection."
  ]
}